INTRODUCTION¶

Breast cancer is caused by the abnormal growth of cells in the breast tissue, which is known as a tumor. Tumors can be benign, pre-malignant, or malignant. Breast cancer mostly affects women. One in every eight women will acquire breast cancer during their lifetime. As a result, early detection of breast cancer is critical for a favorable prognosis and without early detection, the patient will die. The earlier the detection of breast cancer, the better the chance of survival. My project will help to create a classifier that can help diagnose patients and predict the likelihood of a breast cancer.¶

Feature Selection using Correlation¶

This step will involve evaluating the relationship between each feature and find out which features are highly correlated with each other. The correlated features will then be dropped.

Compactness_mean, concavity_mean and concave points_mean are correlated, and so concavity_mean will be chosen

radius_se, perimeter_se and area_se are correlated, and so area_se will be chosen.

radius_worst, perimeter_worst and area_worst are correlated, and so area_worst will be chosen.

Compactness_worst, concavity_worst and concave points_worst are correlated, and so concavity_worst will be chosen.

Compactness_se, concavity_se and concave points_se are correlated, and so concavity_se will be chosen.

texture_mean and texture_worst are correlated are correlated, and so texture_mean will be chosen.

area_worst and area_mean are correlated, and so area_mean will be chosen.
